import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from tabulate import tabulate
import warnings
warnings.filterwarnings('ignore', category=FutureWarning)

# Load the Excel file
file_path = '/Volumes/DVH Data/Working Dataset/Merged_Dataset&DVH_Converted.xlsx'  # 
factors_df = pd.read_excel(file_path, sheet_name='Factors')
dictionary_df = pd.read_excel(file_path, sheet_name='Dictionary')

# Clean the dictionary dataframe to fill down the Column names
dictionary_df['Column'] = dictionary_df['Column'].fillna(method='ffill')

# Create a mapping dictionary that maintains order based on the 'Code'
ordered_label_dict = {}
for index, row in dictionary_df.iterrows():
    if row['Column'] not in ordered_label_dict:
        ordered_label_dict[row['Column']] = []
    ordered_label_dict[row['Column']].append((row['Code'], row['Label']))

# Convert tuples in lists to dictionaries and sort them by the code
for column, pairs in ordered_label_dict.items():
    ordered_label_dict[column] = dict(sorted(pairs, key=lambda x: x[0]))

# Apply the mapping to the dataframe
for column, mapping in ordered_label_dict.items():
    if column in factors_df.columns:
        factors_df[f"{column}"] = factors_df[column].map(mapping)

factors_df['Drinking History'] = pd.Categorical(factors_df['Drinking History'],
                                                categories=['Non-drinker', 'Ex-drinker', 'Light', 'Moderate', 'Heavy'],
                                                ordered=True)

# Define categorical variables
categorical_vars = ['Sex', 'ECOG', 'Smoking Type', 'Drinking History', 'Disease Site', 
                    'Histological Diagnosis', 'T', 'N', 'M', 'TNM Staging', 'Primary Treatment Modality', 
                    'Treatment Regimen', 'Insurance Status', 'Insurance Type', 'Periodontal Grading', 
                    'HPV', 'Status at Last Follow-up']

# Frequency and relative frequency for categorical variables
def categorical_frequency(df, variable, group_by):
    # Calculate frequency
    freq_table = df.groupby([group_by, variable]).size().unstack(fill_value=0).round(2)
    # Calculate total counts for each group
    freq_table['Total'] = freq_table.sum(axis=1).round(2)
    # Calculate relative frequency
    rel_freq_table = freq_table.div(freq_table['Total'], axis=0).drop(columns=['Total']).round(2)
    return freq_table, rel_freq_table

# Updated printing function using tabulate
def print_table(df, title):
    print(title)
    print(tabulate(df, headers='keys', tablefmt='pretty', floatfmt="0.2f"))
    print("\n")  # Add an extra newline for better spacing

# Plotting function for the first perspective: Variable by ORNJ Status
def plot_data_variable_by_ORNJ(df, variable):
    label_column = f"{variable}"
    freq_table, rel_freq_table = categorical_frequency(df, label_column, 'ORNJ Status')

    ax = rel_freq_table.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(10, 5), stacked=False)
    plt.title(f'Relative Frequency of {variable} by ORNJ Status')
    plt.ylabel('Relative Frequency')
    ax.legend(title=variable)

    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(f"{p.get_height():.2f}", (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha='center', va='bottom')

    plt.show()

    print_table(freq_table, f"Frequency Table for {variable} by ORNJ Status:")
    print_table(rel_freq_table, f"Relative Frequency Table for {variable} by ORNJ Status:")

# Plotting function for the second perspective: ORNJ Status by Variable
def plot_data_ORNJ_by_variable(df, variable):
    label_column = f"{variable}"
    freq_table, rel_freq_table = categorical_frequency(df, 'ORNJ Status', label_column)

    ax = rel_freq_table.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(10, 5), stacked=False)
    plt.title(f'Relative Frequency of ORNJ Status by {variable}')
    plt.ylabel('Relative Frequency')
    ax.legend(title='ORNJ Status')

    for p in ax.patches:
        ax.annotate(f"{p.get_height():.2f}", (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2., p.get_height()), ha='center', va='bottom')

    plt.show()

    print_table(freq_table, f"Frequency Table for ORNJ Status by {variable}:")
    print_table(rel_freq_table, f"Relative Frequency Table for ORNJ Status by {variable}:")

# Processing categorical variables
for categorical_variable in categorical_vars:
    if f"{categorical_variable}" in factors_df.columns:
        plot_data_variable_by_ORNJ(factors_df, categorical_variable)
        plot_data_ORNJ_by_variable(factors_df, categorical_variable)
